2026-03-23T20:35:35.995Z JOY-004A comment.added "Topics to cover: (1) Config cascade (config.yaml > global > defaults > code) with concrete examples. (2) project.yaml governance as separate axis that caps the resolved config value. (3) joy config output showing value source and capping. (4) Effective interaction level display in joy show. Consider a dedicated Config Reference page or a section in the Tutorial." [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-23T20:38:48.218Z JOY-0047 comment.added "Decision: Replace numeric levels 1-5 with named levels. Mapping: 1=autonomous, 2=supervised, 3=collaborative, 4=interactive, 5=pairing. Names form a clear progression from agent-driven to human-driven. Internally the ordering is preserved for min/max comparisons (autonomous < supervised < ... < pairing). Config, project.yaml, and AI instructions will use these names. Numeric input may be accepted as shorthand but named levels are canonical." [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-23T20:40:57.442Z JOY-0047 comment.added "Implementation note: Named levels must be prominently documented in AI instructions (.joy/ai/instructions.md). The level descriptions are among the most important parts of the AI collaboration rules -- they define HOW the agent works with the human. We will finalize the wording for each level together before writing the instructions." [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
